    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 1988 Porsche 911 Carrera 3.2 is a superlative example of air-cooled engineering, featuring the coveted Getrag G50 five-speed manual transaxle with Borg-Warner synchronizers for superior shift indexing. The numbers-matching 3.2L flat-six utilizes Bosch Motronic DME for optimized ignition timing and fuel delivery, showing zero signs of oil migration or vacuum leaks. The suspension maintains its factory torsion bar setup, offering the precise kinematic feedback and roll stiffness expected of a concours-level chassis. Every component, from the staggered Fuchs alloy wheels to the unblemished heat exchangers, reflects a rigorous maintenance protocol. This is a turn-key, investment-grade vehicle with a pristine undercarriage and a mechanically quiet valvetrain.",
